The paper discusses the SP theory of intelligence and its realisation in the SP computer model, which simplifies and integrates concepts across artificial intelligence and related areas. The paper also discusses the potential applications of the SP system in several areas, including big data, autonomous robots, medical diagnosis, and more. Given this content, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses aspects of reasoning and planning, which are relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and the potential for the SP system to serve as a database, which is relevant to cs.DB (Databases).
